WEBVTT

00:03.737 --> 00:05.070
- Hey.

00:05.072 --> 00:06.338
- Hey.

00:06.340 --> 00:09.241
I gotta say, you run
a very nice operation.

00:09.243 --> 00:12.177
- Oh, come on, you've never got
food catered to the district?

00:12.179 --> 00:14.079
- Yeah, once.

00:14.081 --> 00:17.516
This old man, he left
his inheritance of $530

00:17.518 --> 00:19.752
to the district, so we got
Al's Beef for everybody.

00:19.754 --> 00:21.353
- [laughs]
Oh, gosh.

00:21.355 --> 00:23.655
that you wouldn't have to pay
for anything.

00:23.657 --> 00:26.792
Now you get written up
for taking a stick of gum.

00:26.794 --> 00:28.527
- Lis, Brianna and Jay.
- Hi.

00:28.529 --> 00:30.429
- Listen, I just came
from Chicago Med.

00:30.431 --> 00:32.031
- We're having a boy.

00:32.033 --> 00:34.533
- Congratulations. Congrats.
- That's amazing.

00:34.535 --> 00:35.801
- Thanks, man.
- Congrats.

00:35.803 --> 00:37.336
- That's beautiful.
Oh!

00:37.338 --> 00:39.171
- Thank you.

00:39.173 --> 00:40.205
- Wonderful.

00:40.207 --> 00:42.474
- Thank you.
You have kids?

00:42.476 --> 00:45.210
- No, I haven't really
found the time for that.

00:45.212 --> 00:47.513
- Are you married?

00:47.515 --> 00:49.481
- I haven't really found
the time for that either.

00:49.483 --> 00:51.750
- Well, you should
find the time.

00:51.752 --> 00:53.419
- I gotta steal him
and do a bank run.

00:53.421 --> 00:55.421
- Yeah, yeah.
- Congrats again.

00:55.423 --> 00:56.422
- Thank you.

00:56.424 --> 00:57.656
- I'll see you.
- Bye.

01:04.330 --> 01:06.498
- Hope Lissa didn't corner you
about being a bachelor.

01:06.500 --> 01:09.201
- No, it's all good.

01:09.203 --> 01:12.304
- 263,000.

01:16.209 --> 01:17.776
Let's roll.

01:22.082 --> 01:24.216
Heath.

01:24.218 --> 01:26.085
- Ma'am.

01:26.087 --> 01:28.353
- Here.

01:28.355 --> 01:31.523
You're the only one
with the safety deposit box key.

01:31.525 --> 01:33.425
I don't know what you're doing
for dinner later,

01:33.427 --> 01:35.794
but if you want,
we can do Maestro's.

01:37.297 --> 01:39.398
- Um, so I'm kind of--

01:39.400 --> 01:41.567
- Jay.
[chuckles]

01:41.569 --> 01:43.202
It's just dinner.

01:43.204 --> 01:44.603
I'm going through
a complicated divorce,

01:44.605 --> 01:46.705
so we can keep it simple.

01:48.775 --> 01:51.243
[engine turns over]

01:57.117 --> 01:59.251
- Playing "hard to get"
with the boss lady, huh?

01:59.253 --> 02:01.286
- All right, just concentrate
on the road.

02:01.288 --> 02:04.356
Couple years ago,
I was a DEA agent,

02:04.358 --> 02:06.258
putting pot dealers
in prison.

02:06.260 --> 02:07.759
Now I'm driving their cash
to the bank.

02:07.761 --> 02:11.363
- For 100 bucks an hour.
It's a brave new world.

02:11.365 --> 02:14.366
- Do you know how many 12,
13-year-old corner boys

02:14.368 --> 02:16.735
I've seen die
over a dime bag?

02:16.737 --> 02:19.671
In my opinion, the faster
they legalize it, the better.

02:19.673 --> 02:21.373
- I hear that.

02:23.000 --> 02:29.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:30.683 --> 02:32.851
[tires screeching]

02:34.320 --> 02:36.255
- What the hell
is this guy doing?

02:36.257 --> 02:38.624
- Iowa plates.
They must be lost.

02:38.626 --> 02:39.858
- Let's just
get to the bank.

02:49.335 --> 02:51.637
Reverse!
Reverse!

02:51.639 --> 02:53.906
[tires screeching]

02:53.908 --> 02:56.909
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

02:56.911 --> 03:05.284
<i>♪</i>

03:06.386 --> 03:07.586
Move! Move!

03:07.588 --> 03:08.887
Terry, leave it!
Leave it!

03:17.897 --> 03:20.899
[gunfire continues]

03:20.901 --> 03:22.734
<i>♪</i>

03:22.736 --> 03:24.236
Terry, no!

03:24.238 --> 03:25.504
- Aah!

03:25.506 --> 03:29.208
<i>♪</i>

03:29.210 --> 03:31.510
- Terry!
Terry!

03:31.512 --> 03:32.711
[groans]

03:32.713 --> 03:34.279
It's gonna be okay.

03:34.281 --> 03:36.315
Hold on, hold on, brother,
hold on, hold on.

03:36.317 --> 03:38.350
10-1! 10-1!
This is Detective Jay Halstead.

03:38.352 --> 03:40.919
I'm at Canal and Van Buren.
We're taking heavy fire.

03:40.921 --> 03:42.921
Shots fired! Shots fired!
We got a man shot!

03:42.923 --> 03:44.656
<i>[indistinct radio chatter]</i>

03:44.658 --> 03:46.792
- Get up.
Come on, come on.

03:46.794 --> 03:49.628
<i>♪</i>

03:49.630 --> 03:50.829
Go, go, go.

03:50.831 --> 03:53.498
[tires screeching]

03:53.500 --> 03:54.900
<i>♪</i>

03:54.902 --> 03:56.335
- It's gonna be okay.

03:56.337 --> 03:57.703
It's gonna be okay.
They're coming, okay?

03:57.705 --> 03:59.638
- [groans]
- Terry, stay with me.

03:59.640 --> 04:00.772
Stay with me,
stay with me.

04:00.774 --> 04:01.773
- Not like this, brother.

04:01.775 --> 04:03.809
- Hey, Terry,
you're good, bro.

04:03.811 --> 04:06.378
You're good, stay with me.
- [groaning]

04:13.586 --> 04:15.921
- He's still got a pulse,
just get him to Med.

04:15.923 --> 04:17.389
- Were you able to see
a license plate on the truck?

04:17.391 --> 04:18.957
- There's wasn't one.
- Okay.

04:18.959 --> 04:20.926
<i>[tense music]</i>

04:20.928 --> 04:22.761
Now, what--
- Where the hell were you?

04:22.763 --> 04:25.330
- I was pinned.
My piece jammed.

04:25.332 --> 04:27.299
- It jammed? How the hell does
a DEA tough guy run and hide?

04:27.301 --> 04:30.502
- Huh?
- Hey, Jake. Hey, easy, easy.

04:30.504 --> 04:32.671
- Hey, I don't want to see your
face again, do you understand?

04:32.673 --> 04:34.539
- Easy!

04:34.541 --> 04:36.308
<i>♪</i>

04:36.310 --> 04:37.909
Just calm down.
- Well, he was--

04:37.911 --> 04:39.311
he was ducking, man.

04:39.313 --> 04:42.814
- I don't care about him.
Are you okay?

04:42.816 --> 04:44.016
<i>♪</i>

04:44.018 --> 04:46.318
- I'm fine.
I mean, I hit him, but I'm fine.

04:46.320 --> 04:47.519
- All right,
just take a breath.

04:47.521 --> 04:50.522
<i>♪</i>

04:50.524 --> 04:54.760
- Looks like they left behind
a .40 caliber breadcrumb.

04:54.762 --> 04:56.895
- I shot one of 'em.
He must have dropped it.

04:56.897 --> 04:57.896
- Yeah.

04:57.898 --> 05:06.038
<i>♪</i>

05:10.410 --> 05:11.476
- Hey.

05:11.478 --> 05:13.712
- I'll get this to the lab.
- Yeah.

05:13.714 --> 05:15.514
- I heard on the scanner.

05:15.516 --> 05:18.650
- Erin, I'm okay.
Is there word from Med on Terry?

05:19.919 --> 05:21.553
- Not yet.

05:24.657 --> 05:27.726
Come on.

05:32.865 --> 05:35.801
- You're not
taking me off this.

05:35.803 --> 05:39.504
- I'm gonna do whatever I feel
is right for this unit, Jay.

05:41.107 --> 05:44.710
- This is Terry's blood.

05:44.712 --> 05:47.646
I saw the guy who shot him.

05:47.648 --> 05:50.082
You need me.

05:50.084 --> 05:52.050
- [sighs]

05:52.052 --> 05:55.087
Okay.

05:55.089 --> 05:57.389
But anytime I tell you
to sit on the sidelines,

05:57.391 --> 05:59.591
you're gonna sit,
you understand?

06:04.397 --> 06:06.832
- My family warned me about
getting into this business.

06:06.834 --> 06:08.667
- You're a lawyer?
- I am.

06:08.669 --> 06:11.403
before getting
into the marijuana trade?

06:11.405 --> 06:15.807
- Bit of an unconventional jump,
wouldn't you say?

06:15.809 --> 06:17.609
- I was under the impression
you were investigating

06:17.611 --> 06:19.611
a robbery, not me.

06:19.613 --> 06:22.047
- We have to check
every box.

06:24.484 --> 06:27.386
- The federal government
classifies marijuana

06:27.388 --> 06:30.021
as a controlled substance,

06:30.023 --> 06:32.791
so I don't have access
to our country's banking system.

06:32.793 --> 06:36.728
That's why every week,
I deposit a quarter mil, cash,

06:36.730 --> 06:38.930
into a safety deposit box
at Chase,

06:38.932 --> 06:42.467
so I really don't think
I'm gonna steal it from myself.

06:42.469 --> 06:43.935
- Who else knows
the bank route?

06:43.937 --> 06:46.037
- Just my security team,
and since one of your own,

06:46.039 --> 06:48.006
Jay Halstead,
is in charge of that,

06:48.008 --> 06:49.674
I think we can
rule out that angle.

06:49.676 --> 06:50.942
- We're gonna have to run
background checks

06:50.944 --> 06:52.010
on all of your employees.

06:52.012 --> 06:53.712
- I already do that.

06:53.714 --> 06:56.948
- We understand,
but we haven't.

06:56.950 --> 06:58.850
What about
disgruntled employees?

06:58.852 --> 07:00.919
- I pay three times the minimum
wage to all of my workers.

07:00.921 --> 07:04.890
- Hey.
- Imagine a lot of the gangs...

07:04.892 --> 07:07.759
- Got a call from Med.

07:07.761 --> 07:10.829
Terry, he didn't make it.

07:10.831 --> 07:12.998
Massive hemorrhaging.

07:13.000 --> 07:15.967
<i>[tense music]</i>

07:15.969 --> 07:21.640
<i>♪</i>

07:21.642 --> 07:22.808
Listen, man,
why don't you take

07:22.810 --> 07:25.811
some of those vacation days
we never use?

07:25.813 --> 07:29.181
<i>♪</i>

07:29.183 --> 07:31.650
Get your head right.

07:31.652 --> 07:38.957
<i>♪</i>

07:38.959 --> 07:40.459
- [chuckles]
I don't have one.

07:40.461 --> 07:41.827
- [laughs]
That's perfect.

07:41.829 --> 07:44.463
That's hilarious.
[laughs]

07:44.465 --> 07:47.232
- It's not like, you know,
I need to do it, right?

07:47.234 --> 07:48.700
- You guys get anymore
eyewitness statements

07:48.702 --> 07:50.902
from the shooting?

07:50.904 --> 07:52.671
- We gave everything
to Detective Olinsky.

07:52.673 --> 07:54.906
- Yeah.

07:54.908 --> 07:56.074
- All right, well,
you get anything else,

07:56.076 --> 07:57.742
you run it upstairs.

08:00.046 --> 08:01.513
- Okay.

08:04.083 --> 08:06.685
Who put stripes
on his sleeve?

08:06.687 --> 08:09.588
- Oh, what shenanigans am I
missing here on the playground?

08:09.590 --> 08:11.923
- Uh, nothing.

08:11.925 --> 08:13.492
Sean and I, we were
just gonna follow up

08:13.494 --> 08:14.793
on a burglary
on Roosevelt, so.

08:14.795 --> 08:18.096
- No, you are detailed
to intelligence.

08:18.098 --> 08:20.699
- Great,
loaned out once again.

08:20.701 --> 08:22.901
- You got a problem, Roman?

08:22.903 --> 08:25.070
I got cars in the motor pool
need washing.

08:25.072 --> 08:28.006
- No.
No, we're good, right?

08:28.008 --> 08:30.108
- Right.
- Yeah.

08:30.110 --> 08:32.910
That's what I thought.

08:37.884 --> 08:40.986
- Hey.
I just heard about Terry.

08:40.988 --> 08:42.020
- Yeah.

08:42.022 --> 08:43.221
- I can't help
but feel responsible

08:43.222 --> 08:44.222
for what happened to him.

08:44.224 --> 08:46.191
- You're not.

08:46.193 --> 08:47.893
I am.

08:48.961 --> 08:51.796
- Please tell
Terry's wife

08:51.798 --> 08:54.533
that I'll take care of
all the funeral costs.

08:54.535 --> 08:58.036
- He was a marine, so he'll get
a military send-off.

08:58.038 --> 09:00.305
- Okay.

09:00.307 --> 09:03.575
- Jay, we got something
off the gun.

09:03.577 --> 09:05.877
- You should stay low
until we find these guys,

09:05.879 --> 09:07.812
just in case.

09:07.814 --> 09:09.915
- Okay.

09:10.950 --> 09:13.218
If there's anything
I can do...

09:13.220 --> 09:16.888
- I'm sure we'll have
more questions.

09:16.890 --> 09:18.990
- Thanks.

09:23.930 --> 09:26.965
- I got the lab to do
a rush order,

09:26.967 --> 09:29.834
and they managed to pull
a partial print off the clip

09:29.836 --> 09:32.003
inside the .40 SIG
that was left at the scene.

09:32.005 --> 09:36.841
Now, it came up matching
to a one Joseph "Joey" Ortiz.

09:36.843 --> 09:38.944
- Ortiz?
Yeah, he's a known member

09:38.946 --> 09:40.979
of the Insane King lick crew.
They don't sell drugs.

09:40.981 --> 09:42.981
Their M.O. is to follow
cartel mules

09:42.983 --> 09:45.617
with large amounts of money
after big drug deals,

09:45.619 --> 09:47.352
then they rob 'em.

09:47.354 --> 09:48.353
- Hm.

09:48.355 --> 09:50.355
- Sound familiar, Jay?

09:50.357 --> 09:54.359
- Right, put out
an investigative alert on Ortiz.

09:54.361 --> 09:56.728
Have patrol saturate
all known areas

09:56.730 --> 09:58.863
him and his crew
frequents.

09:58.865 --> 10:03.034
So I gotta ask you.

10:03.036 --> 10:06.237
You sleeping
with this woman?

10:06.239 --> 10:08.373
- Brianna?
- Mm.

10:08.375 --> 10:10.275
- No,
and even if I was,

10:10.277 --> 10:11.843
what would that
have to do with anything?

10:11.845 --> 10:15.380
- All right,
one more time.

10:15.382 --> 10:17.282
You sleeping with her?

10:17.284 --> 10:19.117
<i>[tense music]</i>

10:19.119 --> 10:20.952
- No.

10:20.954 --> 10:25.290
<i>♪</i>

10:25.292 --> 10:28.259
- 2113 Squad, be advised
we're on patrol in the area

10:28.261 --> 10:30.228
of the investigative alert
lodged by intelligence.

10:30.230 --> 10:31.229
Can you hold us down?

10:31.231 --> 10:33.865
<i>- Copy that, 2113.</i>

10:33.867 --> 10:35.967
- No.
- Okay.

10:38.838 --> 10:41.373
[keys clacking]

10:41.375 --> 10:44.309
Nothing?
- No.

10:44.311 --> 10:46.411
- [sighs]

10:54.687 --> 10:55.987
- Whoa, back up.

10:55.989 --> 10:58.256
- What is it?
It's Ortiz's car.

10:58.258 --> 10:59.391
- Roll back,
keep eyes on it.

10:59.393 --> 11:01.259
- Yeah.

11:08.401 --> 11:11.369
- So, what's Ruzek's problem?

11:11.371 --> 11:14.673
- I don't know.
He's got a short fuse.

11:16.275 --> 11:18.309
And he gets jealous.

11:18.311 --> 11:19.878
- What's he got
to be jealous of?

11:19.880 --> 11:21.279
We're partners.

11:21.281 --> 11:25.283
- Yeah, I know, right,
that's what I'm saying.

11:25.285 --> 11:27.385
Forget it.

11:28.821 --> 11:32.123
J--no.

11:32.125 --> 11:34.292
- That's him,
that's Ortiz.

11:34.294 --> 11:36.361
- 2113, be advised
we are on-scene

11:36.363 --> 11:39.197
and located
our robbery offender.

11:39.199 --> 11:41.399
Advise intelligence
we'll throw an anchor down.

11:41.401 --> 11:43.334
<i>- Copy that, 2113.</i>

11:43.336 --> 11:47.172
<i>[tense music]</i>

11:47.174 --> 11:49.140
- Get your guns
on the front door.

11:49.142 --> 11:50.742
Kevin,
get the Chicago bar.

11:50.744 --> 11:52.410
- Got it.

11:52.412 --> 11:53.978
- Okay.

11:53.980 --> 12:01.386
<i>♪</i>

12:01.388 --> 12:02.821
- [grunts]

12:02.823 --> 12:04.756
- All right, go, go.

12:04.758 --> 12:05.857
- [groaning]
- Tell me!

12:05.859 --> 12:08.359
- Chicago police!
Drop it! Drop it!

12:08.361 --> 12:11.229
Now, do it!
Back away.

12:11.231 --> 12:12.764
Back away!
Turn around.

12:12.766 --> 12:14.866
- Turn around.
- Turn around!

12:14.868 --> 12:16.801
- Clear.
- Clear.

12:16.803 --> 12:18.470
- What's good, big homie?

12:18.472 --> 12:20.805
Come on, get down, get down.
You too, bro.

12:20.807 --> 12:23.475
you never saw my face,
you understand me?

12:27.246 --> 12:29.147
- Seems your pal
you were slicing up

12:29.149 --> 12:31.750
is too scared to talk.
Who is he?

12:31.752 --> 12:34.753
- Sasso.
<i>Mi primo.</i>

12:34.755 --> 12:36.221
- That's how you treat
your cousin?

12:36.223 --> 12:38.823
- Just settling
a little family feud.

12:38.825 --> 12:42.460
- What, you didn't want to give
Sasso his cut from the robbery?

12:42.462 --> 12:45.830
- You keep talking about
some robbery I never heard of.

12:45.832 --> 12:47.899
But 260 Gs?

12:47.901 --> 12:51.269
Hell, I wish I had known
about it first.

12:51.271 --> 12:53.538
- .40 caliber with your prints
was left at the scene.

12:53.540 --> 12:55.406
That's some coincidence.

12:55.408 --> 12:57.542
- Talk to Sasso.
He's my alibi.

12:57.544 --> 12:59.144
- [laughs softly]
Your cousin you had

12:59.146 --> 13:01.412
on the table, he's gonna
cover for you?

13:01.414 --> 13:03.148
- You understand, <i>mijo.</i>

13:03.150 --> 13:05.517
We got our own way of dealing
with family in Humboldt Park.

13:05.519 --> 13:07.152
- Get up!

13:07.154 --> 13:09.154
[both grunting]

13:09.156 --> 13:11.356
We know how you make a living
ripping off drug dealers.

13:11.358 --> 13:13.258
Now you're looking
at murder!

13:13.260 --> 13:16.561
- We got our own way of dealing
with things too, <i>mijo.</i>

13:16.563 --> 13:18.163
- [groans]
All right.

13:18.165 --> 13:19.430
All right!

13:19.432 --> 13:21.366
<i>[tense music]</i>

13:21.368 --> 13:24.202
I had a bag of guns stolen
out of my car last week,

13:24.204 --> 13:27.405
so somebody's gotta be
trying to set me up!

13:27.407 --> 13:28.973
- You're gonna
tell me the truth.

13:28.975 --> 13:30.241
- Jay.

13:30.243 --> 13:32.010
<i>♪</i>

13:32.012 --> 13:34.245
You're gonna want
to see this.

13:34.247 --> 13:37.582
Turns out Ortiz's cousin Sasso
is a runner for the cartels

13:37.584 --> 13:40.285
and was gonna give Ortiz up
for robbing their cash drop,

13:40.287 --> 13:42.320
so it looks like Ortiz
was just giving him

13:42.322 --> 13:44.222
a gentle reminder
to keep his mouth shut.

13:44.224 --> 13:47.125
- Okay, so, I pulled this
from a Zac's Beef parking lot

13:47.127 --> 13:48.159
up on Clark and Ridge.

13:48.161 --> 13:49.160
Now, if you look
at the time code

13:49.162 --> 13:50.395
on the actual footage,

13:50.397 --> 13:53.998
- I don't know, bro, I don't see
Ortiz and his boys making it

13:54.000 --> 13:56.067
from Ridge down to Van Buren
in that kind of time.

13:56.069 --> 14:00.972
- No, that .40 SIG was left
there on purpose to mislead us.

14:00.974 --> 14:02.540
- Well, the DNA
from the blood splatter

14:02.542 --> 14:04.609
at the robbery scene
came back inconclusive,

14:04.611 --> 14:06.377
doesn't match any offenders
in the system,

14:06.379 --> 14:08.947
and the '96 Chevy
that was lit on fire,

14:08.949 --> 14:10.882
pushed over the overpass,

14:10.884 --> 14:12.383
stolen from a junkyard
a week ago.

14:12.385 --> 14:14.018
- We didn't get anything
from the shell casings?

14:14.020 --> 14:16.888
- No, all clean.
No prints, every last one.

14:16.890 --> 14:19.057
- All right, kick Ortiz.

14:19.059 --> 14:20.491
- No, I'm not done
talking to him.

14:20.493 --> 14:22.927
- Well, he's not our guy,
his cousin isn't gonna

14:22.929 --> 14:26.030
press charges,
so kick him.

14:28.567 --> 14:31.603
- Jay, talk me through
this route again.

14:31.605 --> 14:33.571
- There's nothing
to talk through.

14:33.573 --> 14:35.139
We change it up
every week.

14:35.141 --> 14:36.908
- All right,
what was last week's route?

14:36.910 --> 14:39.911
- Al, man,
we've been over this.

14:39.913 --> 14:44.949
- Did you or your guys discuss
the route with anyone else?

14:44.951 --> 14:48.052
- For the tenth time, no.

14:48.054 --> 14:51.022
- Well, they found out somehow,
so someone must be talking.

14:51.024 --> 14:52.957
- Or listening.

14:52.959 --> 14:55.193
Hal, go down to your basement,
dig up your old equipment.

14:55.195 --> 14:56.895
I want you to sweep
that dispensary.

14:56.897 --> 14:59.297
- Sweep for bugs? We should be
taking a harder run at Ortiz.

14:59.299 --> 15:03.668
- Jay, take a step back
or go home, it's your call.

15:03.670 --> 15:11.976
<i>♪</i>

15:14.313 --> 15:17.382
- [breathing deeply]

15:19.585 --> 15:21.586
[sniffs]

15:21.588 --> 15:28.559
<i>♪</i>

15:28.561 --> 15:32.030
- Jay.

15:32.032 --> 15:35.266
- Lissa, I'm so sorry.
I'm so sorry.

15:35.268 --> 15:43.374
<i>♪</i>

15:44.543 --> 15:47.612
- You know, when Terry got back
from his last tour,

15:47.614 --> 15:50.081
he was no angel
to deal with.

15:51.517 --> 15:54.118
- Yeah, I know
how that goes.

15:54.120 --> 15:55.653
- It was so hard on him.

15:55.655 --> 15:59.490
Booze, pills,
and then even harder stuff.

15:59.492 --> 16:05.330
His father and brothers tried,
but I nursed him through it,

16:05.332 --> 16:09.534
helped him find
a therapist.

16:09.536 --> 16:12.170
- It sounds like
you really saved him.

16:12.172 --> 16:17.408
<i>♪</i>

16:17.410 --> 16:20.411
- This came last week.

16:20.413 --> 16:23.581
He got into the police academy.

16:23.583 --> 16:26.718
To report next month.

16:26.720 --> 16:29.721
[sobs]

16:29.723 --> 16:35.293
- [chuckles]
Terry, he...

16:35.295 --> 16:39.030
he didn't even mention
he took the exam.

16:39.032 --> 16:40.231
- Maybe he was too proud
to tell you

16:40.233 --> 16:42.600
until it was official.

16:42.602 --> 16:45.570
One thing I know,
he really looked up to you,

16:45.572 --> 16:50.241
said you went through
a lot of the same things.

16:50.243 --> 16:56.214
[sobbing]

16:56.216 --> 16:59.083
<i>♪</i>

16:59.085 --> 17:00.385
- Do you mind
if I keep this?

17:00.387 --> 17:03.221
- I wouldn't know what else
to do with it.

17:03.223 --> 17:05.455
Oh.

17:05.458 --> 17:08.459
[sobbing]
Oh.

17:08.461 --> 17:11.429
<i>♪</i>

17:11.431 --> 17:13.263
[car door closes]

17:16.068 --> 17:18.703
- Is that
a reel-to-reel recorder?

17:18.704 --> 17:20.570
- Yeah, I worked Mayor Daley's
protection detail

17:20.573 --> 17:24.541
Swept his home and office
for bugs once a week.

17:24.544 --> 17:26.544
- I didn't know that.

17:26.546 --> 17:27.612
Learn anything interesting?

17:27.614 --> 17:29.080
- [chuckles]

17:29.082 --> 17:31.282
How a city really runs.

17:34.720 --> 17:39.157
- Al, have you seen Roman
sniffing around Burgess lately?

17:40.492 --> 17:43.795
- Well, they're partners.

17:43.797 --> 17:46.597
I thought you two split up.

17:46.599 --> 17:48.199
- Well, yeah,
but I mean--

17:48.201 --> 17:50.701
- So what do you care?

17:50.703 --> 17:52.804
- What do I care?

17:52.806 --> 17:55.139
Al, she was my fiancée
not two seconds ago,

17:55.141 --> 17:56.207
and it seems like
she's moving on

17:56.209 --> 18:00.311
- Listen, you gotta decide
what kind of cop you want to be.

18:00.313 --> 18:01.512
You want to chase tail,
which is fine--

18:01.514 --> 18:03.247
- Al, it's not tail.
It's Kim.

18:03.249 --> 18:06.684
- Listen, man, kid that
I pulled out of the academy

18:06.686 --> 18:08.519
and assigned to intelligence,

18:08.521 --> 18:11.155
a unit that any young cop
would give his right nut

18:11.157 --> 18:15.660
to be a part of, needs to
figure out his priorities.

18:34.246 --> 18:36.514
- So what exactly
are you looking for?

18:36.516 --> 18:38.883
- RF signals,
transmitters.

18:38.885 --> 18:40.418
- Are you suggesting
that someone

18:40.420 --> 18:42.320
has hacked
into my security system?

18:42.322 --> 18:44.255
- Well, we gotta cover
every angle.

18:44.257 --> 18:45.756
- Hey, I found something.

18:45.758 --> 18:47.191
- What?
What'd you find?

18:47.193 --> 18:48.392
- It's okay, I'm gonna show you.
Follow me.

18:48.394 --> 18:50.294
- I want to know,
what is going on?

18:50.296 --> 18:52.463
- Ma'am, I understand, with
everything that's happening,

18:52.465 --> 18:54.365
you're upset,

18:54.367 --> 18:57.235
but I need you to keep quiet
and follow me, please.

19:01.640 --> 19:04.642
<i>[dark music]</i>

19:04.644 --> 19:12.750
<i>♪</i>

19:43.882 --> 19:50.788
<i>♪</i>

19:50.790 --> 19:52.523
- Hey.

19:52.525 --> 19:54.292
Come here.

19:54.294 --> 19:56.360
Stay here, stay calm.

19:56.362 --> 19:58.196
If the phone rings,
just answer it.

19:58.198 --> 20:01.199
Act natural.
Okay? All right.

20:01.201 --> 20:09.307
<i>♪</i>

20:10.943 --> 20:12.810
- Those bugs aren't cellular.
They're older.

20:12.812 --> 20:14.912
They run on
radio frequency.

20:14.914 --> 20:20.318
- Means whoever's listening
is within a two-block radius.

20:20.320 --> 20:21.752
All right, I'll take north,
you take south.

20:21.754 --> 20:22.753
Keep your phone on.

20:22.755 --> 20:23.754
- Yeah, you got it.

20:23.756 --> 20:25.823
- All right.

20:25.825 --> 20:28.826
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

20:28.828 --> 20:36.934
<i>♪</i>

20:45.577 --> 20:47.445
- Yo, man, what the hell?

20:47.447 --> 20:55.553
<i>♪</i>

20:58.991 --> 21:01.359
- Al, I think I got
something.

21:01.361 --> 21:09.433
<i>♪</i>

21:19.444 --> 21:21.045
- Got serial numbers
off the bugs we found

21:21.047 --> 21:22.480
in Brianna's office.

21:22.482 --> 21:24.915
Called all the spy shops
in Chicago.

21:24.917 --> 21:26.617
Guess who paid for 'em?

21:26.619 --> 21:30.755
- Brianna's soon-to-be
ex-husband, Jason Logan.

21:31.957 --> 21:35.459
- Got his work address here.
JMC Fittings on West Augusta.

21:35.461 --> 21:37.795
- Go pick him up.

21:37.797 --> 21:40.898
Hey, make sure he doesn't
break anything.

21:40.900 --> 21:43.000
- Yeah.

21:44.636 --> 21:45.703
<i>[tool whirring]</i>

21:51.643 --> 21:53.644
- Right there.
- Thank you.

21:53.646 --> 21:59.016
[whirring]

22:01.687 --> 22:04.522
- Can I help you?

22:04.524 --> 22:06.624
- We need to talk.

22:07.993 --> 22:09.794
- I had nothing to do
with Brianna's dispensary

22:09.796 --> 22:11.028
being robbed.

22:11.030 --> 22:12.830
- The dispensary wasn't robbed.
The cash drop

22:12.832 --> 22:15.066
I was in charge of was,
and a man died.

22:15.068 --> 22:16.500
- You think I'd pull
an armed robbery

22:16.502 --> 22:19.070
for over 1/4 mil and
show back up here for shift?

22:19.072 --> 22:20.905
- We know you're suing her
for alimony

22:20.907 --> 22:22.707
in your divorce
settlement.

22:22.709 --> 22:25.876
- I admit, there's no love lost
between me and Brianna.

22:25.878 --> 22:28.579
I mean, the whole idea
for that dispensary was mine.

22:28.581 --> 22:31.048
- Oh, okay, so you think you got
squeezed out of a business deal

22:31.050 --> 22:32.850
that would've put you
in a much higher tax bracket?

22:32.852 --> 22:33.918
- Maybe that's why
you bought the bugs

22:33.920 --> 22:35.519
that we found
in Brianna's office.

22:35.521 --> 22:36.854
That's illegal wire tapping.

22:36.856 --> 22:38.089
More importantly,
that means you heard

22:38.091 --> 22:39.423
our cash drop routes
to the bank,

22:39.425 --> 22:40.658
So along with your partners
in crime,

22:40.660 --> 22:41.826
you're looking
at a homicide.

22:41.828 --> 22:44.528
- Whoa, I didn't bug
her office.

22:44.530 --> 22:47.465
I hired a P.I. to help me
with the alimony case.

22:47.467 --> 22:49.533
He's the one who's
watching Brianna,

22:49.535 --> 22:52.937
to get her to pay up
for sexual abandonment.

22:52.939 --> 22:54.438
- For sexual what?

22:54.440 --> 22:56.540
- Abandonment.

22:56.542 --> 23:00.478
I wanted her bugged 'cause
I knew she was cheating on me.

23:00.480 --> 23:02.513
- So this P.I.,
he's monitoring the calls?

23:02.515 --> 23:06.016
I maxed out my credit cards
'cause he promised me

23:06.018 --> 23:08.853
I'd get a better settlement
if he found dirt on her.

23:08.855 --> 23:10.855
- We're gonna need
the name of this P.I.

23:10.857 --> 23:12.690
- And until that checks out,
we're detaining you

23:12.692 --> 23:14.425
down at the station.
Get up.

23:14.427 --> 23:15.526
You got cuffs?
- Right here.

23:15.528 --> 23:16.894
- Put your hands
behind your back.

23:16.896 --> 23:19.096
Thanks, Jay.
- Yeah.

23:19.098 --> 23:21.832
- Your first name is Jay?
Jay Halstead?

23:21.834 --> 23:22.967
- Yeah, why?

23:22.969 --> 23:24.935
- Heard too many times
on the tapes

23:24.937 --> 23:27.538
how Brianna wants
to screw you.

23:27.540 --> 23:30.541
<i>[tense music]</i>

23:30.543 --> 23:31.809
<i>♪</i>

23:31.811 --> 23:33.411
- Let's go.

23:33.413 --> 23:35.880
<i>♪</i>

23:35.882 --> 23:37.448
This is Frank Amerson,

23:37.450 --> 23:40.451
he's 51, he used to work
as a bail bondsman.

23:40.453 --> 23:43.154
Now he's a P.I. making his bones
spying on cheating spouses.

23:43.156 --> 23:45.823
- You know, I read that
something like 73% of men

23:45.825 --> 23:47.024
mess around
on their wives.

23:47.026 --> 23:48.058
- Where'd you read that?

23:48.060 --> 23:52.463
- They took out the centerfold,
right? What's the point?

23:52.465 --> 23:56.567
- Look, my point is,
Amerson lives in Oak Park,

23:56.569 --> 23:58.102
makes a good living
destroying marriages,

23:58.104 --> 24:00.771
I mean,
why get into armed robbery?

24:00.773 --> 24:03.774
- I've seen
a 65-year-old woman killed

24:03.776 --> 24:05.676
over a $2 lotto scratcher.

24:05.678 --> 24:08.078
We're talking six figures here.

24:08.080 --> 24:09.547
- Yeah, we need
to grab him up.

24:09.549 --> 24:11.782
- I think we should
take a breath,

24:11.784 --> 24:14.618
do our own counter-surveillance,
see if we can make

24:14.620 --> 24:16.620
a concrete connection
to this robbery.

24:16.622 --> 24:18.556
- Look, I can be up on his phone
in, like, two minutes.

24:18.558 --> 24:19.957
- Right, won't take long.

24:19.959 --> 24:23.861
Antonio, you and Ruzek,
get eyes on this Sam Spade.

24:23.863 --> 24:26.564
<i>[indistinct play-by-play]</i>

24:26.566 --> 24:27.898
[approaching footsteps]

24:29.501 --> 24:32.703
- You got anything yet?

24:32.705 --> 24:35.973
- No, just...
[bottles clinking]

24:35.975 --> 24:39.610
A couple of calls from some lady
who thinks her husband

24:39.612 --> 24:42.012
is actually cheating on her...

24:42.014 --> 24:43.948
with her own sister.
[bottle opens]

24:43.950 --> 24:46.984
And the Hawks are down by two

24:46.986 --> 24:48.552
with six minutes to go.

24:48.554 --> 24:50.020
- [sighs]

24:50.022 --> 24:53.123
- So...there's that.

24:54.092 --> 24:56.827
- [sighs]

24:58.230 --> 25:03.167
- That robbery is--
it's pretty crazy, huh?

25:07.239 --> 25:10.541
Bet it brought back
some memories.

25:12.210 --> 25:15.279
- Mouse, I'm good.

25:17.716 --> 25:22.219
<i>- That fireworks show you guys</i>
<i>put on, it's all over the news.</i>

25:22.221 --> 25:23.754
- Yo, it's Amerson.

25:23.756 --> 25:26.824
<i>- Well, things went</i>
<i>as planned.</i>

25:26.826 --> 25:29.693
<i>- Planned? You know</i>
<i>I almost got caught last night,</i>

25:29.695 --> 25:30.961
<i>listening to see</i>
<i>what the cops knew</i>

25:30.963 --> 25:33.664
<i>- Hey, I'll--</i>
<i>I'll call you back.</i>

25:33.666 --> 25:34.999
<i>- I want my cut.</i>

25:35.001 --> 25:37.735
<i>- You'll get yours.</i>

25:37.737 --> 25:39.103
- Let's call Voight.
- Yeah.

25:39.105 --> 25:42.106
<i>[tense music]</i>

25:42.108 --> 25:48.979
<i>♪</i>

25:48.981 --> 25:50.247
- No, no, no, no, no, no.

25:50.249 --> 25:51.815
I wouldn't do that
if I were you.

25:51.817 --> 25:53.250
- Who are you?

25:53.252 --> 25:55.019
- Why so jumpy, Frank?

25:55.021 --> 25:56.720
- I'm watching a husband.

25:56.722 --> 25:59.890
I get made, you never know
how they're gonna react.

25:59.892 --> 26:01.759
I got a concealed permit
for that.

26:01.761 --> 26:03.260
- All right, fantastic,
we'll figure that out

26:03.262 --> 26:04.762
down at the district.

26:04.764 --> 26:07.298
- Why don't you step
out of the car?

26:07.300 --> 26:09.266
<i>- You know I almost</i>
<i>got caught last night,</i>

26:09.268 --> 26:10.801
<i>listening to see</i>
<i>what the cops knew</i>

26:10.803 --> 26:13.971
<i>- Hey, I'll--</i>
<i>I'll call you back.</i>

26:13.973 --> 26:16.941
- Hmm.

26:16.943 --> 26:18.609
Sounds like you need
protection

26:18.611 --> 26:20.277
from the guy on the other end
of that call.

26:20.279 --> 26:23.948
- [laughs and clears throat]
I want a lawyer.

26:23.950 --> 26:26.850
- Glad to call one.

26:26.852 --> 26:29.853
By the time he gets here, you'll
be looking at homicide charges.

26:29.855 --> 26:32.790
- [laughs]

26:32.792 --> 26:34.792
- You were hired
by Brianna's ex-husband

26:34.794 --> 26:37.161
to help
his divorce settlement,

26:37.163 --> 26:40.965
so, you illegally plant
listening devices in her office,

26:40.967 --> 26:44.902
but instead of scandalous gossip
to help his case,

26:44.904 --> 26:46.870
you overhear how much cash
Brianna's moving

26:46.872 --> 26:49.940
and you think, "Hot damn,
I've won the lottery."

26:49.942 --> 26:52.977
- Now the guy you sold
the score to is icing you out.

26:52.979 --> 26:55.079
- [scoffs]

26:57.082 --> 26:58.215
[clears throat]

26:58.217 --> 27:01.352
Uh, If I tell you,
I want protection.

27:05.890 --> 27:08.125
- You give us the guy
on the other end of that call,

27:08.127 --> 27:10.928
I'll rig something up
with the State's Attorney.

27:13.698 --> 27:15.666
- Ahem.

27:15.668 --> 27:20.137
Uh, guy I tracked down
years ago...

27:20.139 --> 27:24.108
when I was a bondsman.
Collin Briggs.

27:24.110 --> 27:28.245
I sold him the score
for 20% of the cash.

27:28.247 --> 27:29.246
- That wasn't so hard, was it?

27:29.248 --> 27:30.247
- [scoffs]

27:30.249 --> 27:31.348
- Who are the others
in his crew?

27:31.350 --> 27:33.050
- I don't know any others
in the crew.

27:33.052 --> 27:35.285
I just know that Briggs
put the crew together.

27:35.287 --> 27:37.087
- Okay.

27:37.089 --> 27:39.056
Call Briggs,
tell him you need to meet,

27:39.058 --> 27:41.225
and if he doesn't show up
with your cut,

27:41.227 --> 27:42.393
you'll go to the police.

27:42.395 --> 27:45.062
- Or you're facing
murder charges.

27:47.265 --> 27:48.265
Come on.

27:48.267 --> 27:50.968
- [sighs]

27:50.970 --> 27:52.403
- Collin Briggs.

27:52.405 --> 27:56.106
He's done time for manslaughter,
aggravated robbery.

27:56.108 --> 27:58.409
According to an FBI database,
he was kicked out

27:58.411 --> 28:01.045
of an anti-government militia
in Indiana.

28:01.047 --> 28:03.914
- Recognize him, Jay?

28:03.916 --> 28:05.916
- Not off the screen.

28:05.918 --> 28:08.886
<i>[tense music]</i>

28:08.888 --> 28:11.989
- Come on,
I'm freezing out here.

28:11.991 --> 28:15.859
- How about you just
think warm thoughts?

28:15.861 --> 28:18.862
[train horn blaring]

28:18.864 --> 28:21.265
<i>♪</i>

28:21.267 --> 28:23.333
Our target has arrived.

28:23.335 --> 28:26.003
[train passing overhead]

28:26.005 --> 28:27.404
- How ya doing, Frank?

28:27.406 --> 28:31.208
Nice night.

28:31.210 --> 28:35.245
- Uh, yeah.
You got my cut?

28:35.247 --> 28:38.348
- You like trains?

28:38.350 --> 28:40.384
[laughs]

28:40.386 --> 28:44.254
<i>♪</i>

28:44.256 --> 28:46.890
- What is Briggs doing?
Should we move in?

28:46.892 --> 28:48.859
- Negative.
Wait till we see the money

28:48.861 --> 28:51.161
or they talk
about the robbery.

28:51.163 --> 28:55.232
- Hear that clatter?

28:55.234 --> 28:57.835
Reminds me of prison gates
being shut.

28:57.837 --> 28:59.837
[train passing overhead]

28:59.839 --> 29:03.474
- You got my 50K or not?

29:03.476 --> 29:05.209
- [laughs]

29:05.211 --> 29:06.744
Sure.

29:06.746 --> 29:08.746
It's in the trunk.

29:08.748 --> 29:16.820
<i>♪</i>

29:18.022 --> 29:21.125
- [screams]

29:22.260 --> 29:24.161
[groaning]

29:24.163 --> 29:27.164
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

29:27.166 --> 29:29.333
<i>♪</i>

29:29.335 --> 29:31.802
[siren blaring]

29:31.804 --> 29:34.805
<i>♪</i>

29:34.807 --> 29:36.006
- Show me your hands!

29:36.008 --> 29:37.007
Show me your hands!

29:37.009 --> 29:39.009
Do it, now!

29:39.011 --> 29:43.981
<i>♪</i>

29:43.983 --> 29:45.816
- You got it?
- Yeah.

29:45.818 --> 29:47.818
Put your hands
behind your back.

29:47.820 --> 29:50.254
<i>♪</i>

29:50.256 --> 29:53.023
Get up.
- Trunk.

29:53.025 --> 29:54.024
- Let me outta here!

29:54.026 --> 29:55.559
- Easy, easy!

29:56.561 --> 29:59.863
You all right?

29:59.865 --> 30:00.964
Come on.

30:05.336 --> 30:08.539
<i>[dark music]</i>

30:08.541 --> 30:10.407
- It wasn't you,

30:10.409 --> 30:13.544
but a guy on your crew
killed my friend.

30:13.546 --> 30:15.913
<i>♪</i>

30:15.915 --> 30:19.049
He had a baby boy
on the way.

30:19.051 --> 30:21.552
- We all need
some pain in our life.

30:21.554 --> 30:25.122
- [exhales]

30:25.124 --> 30:26.924
I'm gonna testify against you
at your trial.

30:26.926 --> 30:31.161
I'm gonna make your life
a living hell.

30:31.163 --> 30:33.397
- Inside a cage
or on the street,

30:33.399 --> 30:35.966
I'm doing time
wherever I stand.

30:35.968 --> 30:38.268
I'll never rat,

30:38.270 --> 30:40.537
so how about you just
go get my jungle juice

30:40.539 --> 30:43.607
and bologna sandwich ready
in my holding cell?

30:43.609 --> 30:47.444
Think you can manage that,
pretty boy?

30:47.446 --> 30:51.415
- It's kind of funny,
the only reason I'm here

30:51.417 --> 30:54.852
is to keep him
from getting to you.

30:54.854 --> 30:56.954
I'm standing over there
thinking about what the hell

30:56.956 --> 31:00.457
I'd do to you
if you talked to me like that.

31:00.459 --> 31:02.526
If there's one thing I hate...

31:02.528 --> 31:06.597
[lock unlatches]
It's a hypocrite.

31:06.599 --> 31:08.599
You got five minutes.

31:08.601 --> 31:16.907
<i>♪</i>

31:17.909 --> 31:21.578
- Take off these cuffs,
let's see.

31:21.580 --> 31:25.048
- Hey, we found them--
rest of the crew.

31:25.050 --> 31:33.156
<i>♪</i>

31:47.171 --> 31:49.172
- Yo, you might want
to hear this.

31:49.174 --> 31:50.540
So the car that Collin Briggs
was driving

31:50.542 --> 31:52.409
belongs to
61-year-old Jacob Seeley.

31:52.411 --> 31:55.112
He lives in Will County, has
a house right outside of Joliet.

31:55.114 --> 31:56.947
- And I did a search,
figuring the car was stolen,

31:56.949 --> 31:58.181
but it wasn't reported,

31:58.183 --> 32:00.284
and guess who Jacob Seeley's
the father of?

32:00.286 --> 32:01.585
- Brendan Seeley.

32:01.587 --> 32:03.086
He did a stretch
in Pontiac

32:03.088 --> 32:04.554
for a string
of strong-armed robberies

32:04.556 --> 32:06.023
where he used a hammer.

32:06.025 --> 32:09.426
Guess who his cellmate was?
Collin Briggs.

32:09.428 --> 32:11.695
- These are the Seeley brothers.

32:11.697 --> 32:13.931
Both have priors
for weapons violations

32:13.933 --> 32:15.465
in Joliet.

32:15.467 --> 32:22.472
<i>♪</i>

32:22.474 --> 32:24.942
- That's him.

32:24.944 --> 32:27.511
That's the guy
that killed Terry.

32:27.513 --> 32:30.147
- Looks like we got
our crew.

32:30.149 --> 32:31.715
- Want me to call
Will County Sheriff?

32:31.717 --> 32:33.450
- Tell 'em
we're on our way.

32:33.452 --> 32:41.525
<i>♪</i>

32:58.476 --> 33:00.544
- That's the truck.

33:00.546 --> 33:08.652
<i>♪</i>

33:16.527 --> 33:19.329
- You do anything stupid,
that hole will be for two.

33:19.331 --> 33:21.131
- Step towards me,
step towards me.

33:21.133 --> 33:23.734
Slowly, nice and slow.

33:23.736 --> 33:25.035
- I tried saving him.

33:25.037 --> 33:26.303
He just kept bleeding.
- Shh.

33:26.305 --> 33:28.238
Where are the others?
Where's Brendan?

33:28.240 --> 33:31.074
- Inside sleeping.

33:31.076 --> 33:33.176
- Antonio, cuff him,
get him outta here.

33:33.178 --> 33:35.045
Keep your ass down.

33:35.047 --> 33:38.048
<i>[tense music]</i>

33:38.050 --> 33:46.123
<i>♪</i>

34:06.477 --> 34:09.446
[floor creaking]

34:09.447 --> 34:17.554
<i>♪</i>

34:23.061 --> 34:25.062
- Give me a reason.

34:25.063 --> 34:29.399
<i>♪</i>

34:29.400 --> 34:32.569
[glass breaking]

34:32.571 --> 34:35.705
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

34:35.706 --> 34:37.706
[dogs barking]

34:37.708 --> 34:39.708
- Police!
Stop!

34:39.710 --> 34:47.818
<i>♪</i>

34:59.564 --> 35:02.566
<i>[tense music]</i>

35:02.568 --> 35:07.637
<i>♪</i>

35:07.639 --> 35:10.107
- [grunting]

35:10.109 --> 35:12.342
<i>♪</i>

35:12.344 --> 35:15.345
[both grunting]

35:15.347 --> 35:23.453
<i>♪</i>

35:34.332 --> 35:35.499
- [grunts]

35:35.501 --> 35:38.301
[screams]

35:38.303 --> 35:41.371
[groaning]

35:41.373 --> 35:44.474
[whimpering]

35:51.749 --> 35:54.851
[choking]

35:56.554 --> 35:58.655
[choking]

36:04.362 --> 36:05.929
[coughs]

36:05.931 --> 36:10.400
[groans]

36:10.402 --> 36:12.636
- I guess I'll call an ambo.

36:12.638 --> 36:15.505
<i>♪</i>

36:15.507 --> 36:17.741
- [gasping]

36:17.743 --> 36:19.342
- Yeah, take your time.

36:19.344 --> 36:22.345
- [coughing]

36:22.347 --> 36:26.449
<i>♪</i>

36:28.352 --> 36:30.754
- Jay.

36:30.756 --> 36:32.556
- We recovered your money,

36:32.558 --> 36:34.224
minus about ten grand

36:34.226 --> 36:36.726
that Briggs and his crew
burned through.

36:36.728 --> 36:40.530
- I don't care about the money.
I'm just glad you're okay.

36:40.532 --> 36:44.568
And the guy that shot Terry?
Did you get him?

36:45.903 --> 36:48.872
- Where he's going, he's never
gonna see the sun again.

36:50.374 --> 36:52.943
- Good.
Terry's wife...

36:52.945 --> 36:55.345
whatever she needs,
any medical expenses

36:55.347 --> 36:57.881
around the baby,
I'll take care of it.

36:57.883 --> 37:01.718
- That's great.
She'll really appreciate that.

37:03.454 --> 37:06.223
- Um, hey, so...

37:06.225 --> 37:10.360
that dinner at Maestro's,
it still stands, the offer.

37:10.362 --> 37:13.230
Could use somebody
to talk to.

37:13.232 --> 37:15.665
- I'm have somebody
waiting for me.

37:15.667 --> 37:16.900
- Oh.

37:16.902 --> 37:19.703
Well, she's a very lucky girl.

37:21.239 --> 37:22.973
- You're gonna need this.
I'm gonna get you the names

37:22.975 --> 37:28.011
of a couple really solid cops--
guys that need the extra money.

37:28.013 --> 37:29.379
- Okay.

37:29.381 --> 37:31.414
- Thank you.

37:31.416 --> 37:33.717
- Hey, if you change your mind,

37:33.719 --> 37:36.353
my door is always open.

37:36.355 --> 37:39.356
<i>[stirring music]</i>

37:39.358 --> 37:43.560
<i>♪</i>

37:43.562 --> 37:48.398
- A time to remain silent
and a time to speak.

37:48.400 --> 37:50.033
<i>♪</i>

37:50.035 --> 37:53.003
There is comfort
in the memories

37:53.005 --> 37:57.641
of how Terry Egan
impacted our lives.

37:57.643 --> 38:03.346
He was a son,
a husband,

38:03.348 --> 38:07.884
a friend,
and a marine.

38:07.886 --> 38:15.992
<i>♪</i>

38:19.063 --> 38:22.465
- So I'm using my belt
as a tourniquet

38:22.467 --> 38:26.636
where his brachial artery
was severed by a sniper round,

38:26.638 --> 38:29.406
and I'm twisting as hard
as I can to staunch blood

38:29.408 --> 38:32.642
and he's throwing up
all over me,

38:32.644 --> 38:35.645
so I say, "Grunt, I'm trying
to save your life here.

38:35.647 --> 38:37.314
- [chuckles]
- [scoffs]

38:37.316 --> 38:38.948
- Anyway, that was
a typical day in Kandahar.

38:38.950 --> 38:40.450
- Mm.

38:40.452 --> 38:42.952
Well, me and Jay,
we was in Korengal.

38:42.954 --> 38:45.355
There was not a day--

38:45.357 --> 38:46.656
day went by
without a firefight.

38:46.658 --> 38:48.391
- Yeah.

38:48.393 --> 38:51.661
- The thing is...

38:51.663 --> 38:53.797
firefights never
scared me.

38:53.799 --> 38:56.900
[bar music playing]

38:56.902 --> 39:00.070
It was coming home.

39:02.106 --> 39:07.844
Having to look into the faces
of the wives and the families...

39:07.846 --> 39:10.780
of the guys that didn't
make it back.

39:13.050 --> 39:17.520
I gotta go, guys.
[clears throat]

39:17.522 --> 39:19.689
- Later.

39:22.393 --> 39:23.393
[knocking at the door]

39:23.395 --> 39:25.495
- Yeah, come in.

39:28.532 --> 39:31.701
- Um, I just wanted
to come in...

39:31.703 --> 39:36.005
and say thank you
for keeping me on the case.

39:36.007 --> 39:38.541
- Well, right now, you're gonna
take a week's medical leave.

39:38.543 --> 39:41.544
- I appreciate it,
but I'm fine, really.

39:41.546 --> 39:44.748
- It's not open
to discussion.

39:44.750 --> 39:47.984
- [sighs]
Thanks.

39:47.986 --> 39:51.087
- Hey, I been meaning
to tell you...

39:54.525 --> 39:57.727
I'm lucky to have you
in my unit.

40:01.399 --> 40:04.401
<i>[tense music]</i>

40:04.403 --> 40:12.475
<i>♪</i>

40:22.753 --> 40:30.860
<i>♪</i>

40:36.801 --> 40:39.803
- [sobbing]

40:39.805 --> 40:47.877
<i>♪</i>

